         "5.0",
         "80.0",
         "Starting in April 2024, UNC5537 used stolen credentials to access Snowflake databases, establishing connections primarily via Mullvad VPN to instances in which two-factor authentication was not enabled. The threat actors subsequently stole data and attempted to extort victims by threatening to publish or sell the victim data. In some cases, the threat actors advertised the data on English- and/or Russian-language underground forums.",
